cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image processing and specifically with removing specular highlights from images. The use of a fully-convolutional neural network (CNN) and the implementation of a multi-class classifier discriminator suggest that this paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of a synthetic dataset designed to help the network generalize well suggests that this paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of an adversarial loss and content loss suggests that this paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the focus on image processing and the use of a neural network suggest that this paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
